// Plan 159 Ф.2 regression guard ([M-reachability-codegen-dce]).
//
// A `requires`/`ensures` contract message may interpolate runtime values
// (`requires amount >= 0, "balance got ${amount}"`). That interpolation desugars
// to an `InterpolatedStr` whose int→str converter + StringBuilder selectors are
// emitted ONLY at the violation site — they never appear syntactically anywhere
// else in this program. Under reachability method-DCE (this file has `main`, so
// it is an executable and DCE is ON) the converter must still be emitted.
//
// Root cause this guards: `lints::collect_used_names` walked `Contract.expr` but
// NOT `Contract.message_expr`, so method-DCE pruned the int→str converter and
// codegen emitted `nova_str` ← `int` (CC-FAIL) at the check site. The fix walks
// `message_expr` for both `Item::Fn` contracts (here) and `Item::Type`
// invariants (see plan140_1/invariant_msg_interp_neg, which guards that path).
//
// Crucially NO other interpolation exists in this file: `println` below takes a
// plain literal. So if the converter is wrongly pruned this CC-FAILs; if kept it
// compiles and the contract fires, rendering the captured value -7.
// EXPECT_RUNTIME_PANIC requires failed: balance got -7 (amount >= 0)

module plan159.f2_contract_msg_interp_dce

fn withdraw(amount int) -> int
    requires amount >= 0, "balance got ${amount}"
=> amount

fn main() Io -> () {
    ro r = withdraw(-7)
    println("UNREACHABLE")
    ro _ = r
}
